Bank of Montreal headquarters in Old Montreal's Place d'Armes






The headquarters of Air Canada


The economy of Quebec is diversified and post-industrial with an average potential for growth.[4] Manufacturing and the Service sectors dominate the economy. If Quebec were a country, its economy would be ranked the 44th largest in the world just behind Norway.[5] Quebec is also ranked the 21st largest in the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development. The economy of Quebec represents 19.65% of the total GDP of Canada.[6]



