MAPLE SYRUP FROM QUÉBEC

Maple Syrup from Québec is produced and sold in several colour classes.

	Our maple syrup varies in colour and flavour in a completely natural way, directly related to the time at which
	it is harvested in the sugaring-off season. Early on, the syrup is usually clear with a slightly sweet taste
	(Golden, Delicate Taste and Amber, Rich Taste). As the season progresses, the syrup becomes darker
	and more caramelized (Dark, Robust Taste and Very Dark, Strong Taste). Maple syrup from Québec contains
	more than a hundred bioactive compounds, and significant quantities of vitamins and minerals.

Golden, Delicate Taste
	This syrup comes from maple sap harvested at the very beginning of the sugaring-off season. It’s distinguished by
	its light golden hue and sweet, delicate flavour. It’s a delicious topping for yogourt and ice cream.

Amber, Rich Taste
	This syrup has a pure, rich taste and a magnificent amber colouring. It’s ideal as an ingredient in vinaigrettes
	and all sorts of dishes and desserts.

Dark, Robust Taste
	This syrup, with its more pronounced, caramelized flavour, is well-suited for cooking, baking, and sauces.
	It’s celebrated for the way it enhances the taste of fruity dishes.

Very Dark, Strong Taste
	This syrup is the product of maple sap harvested at the end of the sugaring-off season. Its flavour, more pronounced
	than any of the previously-listed syrups, is rich and distinctive. It colours and perfumes sauces and glazes to perfection.








MAPLE SUGAR FROM QUÉBEC

Granulated maple sugar from Québec can have the texture
	of table sugar, icing sugar or fructose.

	It’s also found in the form of nuggets. This unique product can be used, in equal quantities,
	as a substitute wherever recipes call for white or brown sugar. The distinctive yet delicate flavour
	of maple sugar from Québec works beautifully in sweets (pastries and fruit desserts,
	for example) as well as in savoury dishes or in tea and coffee.








HARD MAPLE SUGAR (FOR GRATING) FROM QUÉBEC

In compact block form, hard maple sugar from Québec was highly prized
	in years past when it was known as country sugar, home sugar or sap sugar. 

	As it is today…true connaisseurs love it as a garnish, grated on French toast, toast and pancakes.
	Some also put a light dusting of maple sugar on desserts or even meat and poultry dishes,
	adding the subtle taste of maple from Québec.








MAPLE FLAKES FROM QUÉBEC

Maple flakes from Québec are made of freeze-dried, dehydrated maple syrup.

	Maple flakes enhance the taste of cocktails, meat dishes, vegetables, and desserts. They’re also perfect
	in crumb coatings and spice mixtures. Maple flakes from Québec are available plain or flavoured.








MAPLE BUTTER FROM QUÉBEC

Don’t let the name mislead you.
	The ever-popular maple butter contains no butter or dairy.

	It’s actually a fondant, a pastry term which refers to the buttery texture achieved in its preparation of cooking and churning.
	Like all 100% pure Maple Products from Québec, maple butter is made of one sole ingredient: maple sap. It’s perfect for
	topping desserts, pancakes and French toast, adding flavour to custard, or making marzipan with almonds.
	Maple butter is also a successful addition to aromatic preparations such as pesto and pistou.








MAPLE TAFFY FROM QUÉBEC

Maple taffy from Québec is made of maple syrup boiled down to a concentrate.

	At sugaring-off time, a century-old tradition in Québec, hot taffy is poured onto snow to cool, and be enjoyed!
	As with all Maple Products from Québec, taffy is available all year round, in containers large and small.
	Aside from heating and pouring it on the snow, this product should be tried in desserts like Italian meringue
	and pralines. Maple taffy from Québec can also be used to flavour or enhance the taste of salty foods
	like stuffed red meat and poultry.








NAPSI-CERTIFIED MAPLE WATER FROM QUÉBEC

NAPSI-certified maple water is the new rage and will be for years to come,
	both commercially and gastronomically.

	There should be no surprise that maple water from Québec is enjoying tremendous popularity. It holds 46 nutritional
	compounds essential to life, growth, and protection for the tree. It’s a veritable bioactive cocktail with numerous vitamins
	and minerals, organic acids, polyphenols and phytohormones. The best part is that it contains only 5 grams of carbohydrates,
	or 20 calories per 250 ml!

	NAPSI-certified maple water from Québec is first and foremost a pleasure to drink. Its sweet, delicate flavour is quite refreshing. Athletes especially appreciate its hydrating and regenerative properties. Its refined taste, subtle aroma and light sweetness have caught the attention of cooks and bakers at home and in professional kitchens. It has even been noted that maple water creates osmosis that provides the treasured concentration of flavours that brings the fifth savory taste known as “umami.”

	 

NAPSI Certification

Maple water from Québec has its own quality certification called NAPSI, established by the
	Federation of Québec Maple Syrup Producers for the sake of authenticity and quality.



	The harvesting and processing of NAPSI-certified products must meet rigorous standards that ensure food safety,
	whether by the importer, manufacturer, packager, or chef. This seal also guarantees that consumers experience the drinking
	of fresh, crystalline maple water, just as it came out of the tree. NAPSI is an acronym that best describes
	the qualities of maple water from Québec:

Natural, as it comes from maple treesAuthentic, as it is the water that nature brings forth from the treePure, as there are no added agents or ingredientsSterile, as it contains no micro-organismsIntegral, as it is whole, unrefined, with all the compounds that nature gave it

	For more information, go to napsi.ca.








MAPLE SPIRITS FROM QUÉBEC

Fermented maple water or maple-flavoured and blended liqueur, the many types
	of maple spirits from Québec are made to sip or include in your recipes.

	The choice is yours, from dessert wine to whisky liqueur, cream to sparkling…the possibilities
	are as endless as the creativity of their artisans and your spirit of adventure.
	Maple Spirits from Québec are pure joy to discover and explore!








SPECIALTY MAPLE PRODUCTS FROM QUÉBEC

There’s a wealth of local specialty products flavoured with Québec maple.

	Vinaigrettes, vinegars, mustards and jellies, these products are good to go as is, or as accompaniments
	to savory or sweet dishes. The delicate flavour of maple marries particularly well with marinades,
	gourmet salads, terrines and the finest cheeses. It’s a family of excellent products to discover
	and add your personal touch to a meal, for instance, in a unique tapas menu.





 





 Classification guidelines 



	The new government regulations for the classification of maple syrup are now in effect.
	This new grading regime separates maple syrup into two categories and four colour classes.

	As of December 13, 2016, maple products for export are labelled in accordance with the
	new classification system. Containers of maple syrup for sale in Québec, however, may display
	grading by the old or new regulations. Maple producers who sell only in Québec
	have until December 2017 to change the labelling of their products
	to reflect the new classification system.Grade A 
	Grade A maple syrup is obtained only by concentrating maple sap, does not ferment,
	is clear and uniform in colour, is free of objectionable odor or taste,
	and has a maple flavour characteristic of its colour class.Processing Grade
	Processing Grade maple syrup is obtained only by concentrating maple sap,
	ut it does not qualify for Grade A. 

	 



	 

Classification maple products  |  PDF








 Certifications 



Maple Products - Special Certifications

	There are a number of different certifications for Maple Products from Québec, each attesting to
	a particular mode of production and all affirming their superior quality. 


ORGANIC CERTIFICATION

	Since Maple Products from Québec are all-natural and locally-produced, you may well ask what
	the difference is between organically-certified maple syrup and “classic” maple syrup.
	They’re both made in the same fashion. 100% pure Québec maple syrup is produced
	by boiling the maple water, containing about 2% sugar, until it reaches 66 degrees Brix.
	At this density, the maple syrup is stable and resistant to alteration.

	The differences between classic and organic syrup actually reside in the way the sap
	is collected and the product is managed. This involves maintenance of the maple stand,
	the biodiversity requirements, cleaning products for the equipment, auxiliary technology,
	and the proper type of storage containers. Some of these practices have also been adopted
	by classic syrup producers, so they often overlap with those required by organic producers.

	In Québec (as elsewhere), for a product to be certified “organic,” a maple syrup producer
	must complete a certification process usually administered by a province or state, a federal
	government agency or an organization so mandated by the government. Producers accept
	the responsibility to keep records on an ongoing basis and to undergo periodic
	inspections that verify their compliance. Most organic certifications forbid the use
	of non-approved cleaning and disinfection products, among other things.

	Practices must also be undertaken to protect the health of maple stands, including a limited
	number of taps per tree. The producer working organically observes standards that ensure
	the entire process and all practices related to the health of the sugar bush are designed
	to improve product quality and environmental sustainability. Producers with organic
	certification commit to respect these requirements, ensuring that consumers who
	choose to buy organic food are getting what they want. It bears noting that Canadian
	regulations on organic production are amongst the most stringent in the world.



KOSHER CERTIFICATION

	Maple Products from Québec that are certified kosher meet the requirements of Jewish dietary law.
	All production steps and all equipment used are inspected by a rabbi, who ensures that every
	element that comes into contact with the maple products are also certified as kosher.
	This includes the equipment, the cleaners used to wash it and the various additives
	that stabilize the foam at the time of boiling.



NAPSI-CERTIFIED MAPLE WATER

	NAPSI is a certification for maple water. It was established by the Federation of Québec
	Maple Syrup Producers in 2013, after several years of research. This certification guarantees
	a taste experience that’s like a drink freshly-drawn from the maple tree.

	Québec’s own NAPSI certification ensures a clear, translucent appearance, with freshness and beneficial
	properties long-provided by the maple tree…as represented by the NAPSI acronym:

Natural Authentic Pure Sterile Integral

				• Harvest of maple water from the forest, and storage

				• Transport of maple water from site to processing plant

				• Stabilization of maple water

				• Bottling of maple water

				• Authentication of finished product

	 

	For more information on maple water and NAPSI certification, go to napsi.ca.



OTHER CERTIFICATIONS

	Some processors hold quality certifications such as SQF, BRC FOOD and FSSC 22 000.
	Find out more in the Products and Suppliers sections.



Organic Kosher NAPSI Other 







 Health benefits 



Maple and your Health

	More and more, people are making healthy choices, a trend which is only bound to get stronger. In addition
	to being 100% natural with no artificial colouring or flavours, Maple Products from Québec are full of vitamins
	and minerals. They also possess antioxidants at a level comparable to many fruits and vegetables.
	No wonder the natural properties and components of maple products are at the heart
	of research work in Québec and abroad.

The Federation of Québec Maple Syrup Producers does not encourage increased consumption of sugar.
	Used in moderation, pure maple products are an attractive option when compared to other natural sweeteners. 

	 




	 

NUTRITIONAL VALUE THAT PACKS A PUNCH!

	All sugars are not equal. Maple Products from Québec contain more vitamins and minerals than honey, agave syrup and white sugar. A 60 ml (1/4 cup) portion of maple syrup satisfies more than 100% of the recommended daily dosage of manganese, 37% of riboflavin, 18% of zinc, 7% of magnesium and 5% of calcium and potassium.

Download the nutritional facts  |  PDF



	 

ANTIOXIDANT WARRIORS

	100% pure Maple Products from Québec also contain 65 different antioxidants, nine of which
	are unique to them. These polyphenols, trace elements and vitamins position maple products amongst
	fruits and vegetables for nutritional value. For example, the antioxidant efficacy of maple products
	is comparable to that of tomatoes, broccoli and bananas. A 60 ml (1/4 cup) serving of syrup, depending on
	its colour, supplies from 10% to 38% of the recommended daily dosage of antioxidants. Take note that
	the darker the maple syrup, the more power it packs as an antioxidant.

Download the nutritional facts  |  PDF



	 

A COMPETITIVE GLYCEMIC INDEX

	The glycemic index of Maple Products from Québec is equivalent to that of agave syrup, corn syrup,
	honey, and Kuromitsu. Studies, however, reveal great variability in the value of
	the glycemic index from person to person.



NUTRITIONAL VALUE THAT PACKS A PUNCH! ANTIOXIDANT WARRIORS  A COMPETITIVE GLYCEMIC INDEX 












 Sports nutrition 



A True Champion: Maple and Sports Nutrition

	Maple is not only for the pleasures of the table. Maple Products from Québec are the winner’s
	choice before, during and after training. Professional and amateur athletes are pushing their limits
	to new levels with this superior-quality, all-natural source of energy.


	 

WHY MAPLE PRODUCTS FROM QUÉBEC?

1. They are quickly metabolized.
	Maple products provide simple carbohydrates that easily metabolize glucose,
	acting as fuel during exercise.

2. They are antioxidants. 
	Maple products contain 63 antioxidant compounds. A 60 ml (¼ cup) portion
	of maple syrup stimulates as much antioxidant activity as a tomato or raw broccoli.
	Antioxidants protect cells against oxidative stress caused by the free radicals
	produced during intense exercise.

3. They’re rich in electrolytes.
	Maple products contain potassium, an electrolyte that helps balance fluids
	and maintain normal muscle function. The more physical your workout, the more you need
	to replace the electrolytes lost due to heavy perspiration.

4. They’re ideal for long training sessions.
	Maple products can contribute to increased strength by providing an immediate
	source of energy to keep up the pace.

5. They promote muscle recovery.
	Maple products are an excellent source of manganese and zinc, minerals vital to muscle recovery.
	A 60 ml (¼ cup) portion of maple syrup fills 100% of the daily need for manganese and 18%
	of the recommended daily dosage of zinc. Maple products are richer than
	other sugars in manganese and zinc.

6. They rebuild your reserves.
	After training, maple products help the body recuperate and
	renew its glycogen reserves.



	 

NAPSI-CERTIFIED MAPLE WATER:
	HYDRATE NATURALLY WITH THIS EXCEPTIONAL PRODUCT! !

	NAPSI-certified Maple Water from Québec is another locally-produced specialty.
	It contains 46 nutrients, including several vitamins and minerals, and only 5 grams of carbohydrates,
	or 25 calories per 250 ml serving. Hydrating and regenerating, and so refreshing during
	or after physical activity, it can be taken on its own or mixed with an energy drink.
	Athletes love its slightly sweet and delicate flavour.

	To learn more about maple water and the NAPSI certification, please visit napsi.ca.



WHY MAPLE PRODUCTS FROM QUÉBEC? NAPSI-CERTIFIED MAPLE WATER: HYDRATE NATURALLY WITH THIS EXCEPTIONAL PRODUCT! 







 The secret ingredient 



Maple: From our Forest to your Table

	While Maple Products from Québec are becoming more and more known for their health benefits,
	chefs and food-lovers are falling for their unique flavour. Their sweet and incomparable taste and
	scent improves whatever dish it graces. Did you know that Maple Products from Québec even
	stimulate umami, the “fifth taste” whose discovery has revolutionized the culinary world?


	 

MAPLE AND UMAMI

	Umami is one of the five basic tastes, along with salty, sweet, bitter, and sour.

	In contrast to the other tastes, umami (meaning pleasant savory taste in Japanese) is more complex
	to describe and understand. One theory says Maillard reactions cause perception of the umami taste.
	These are chemical reactions that occur between amino acids and sugar when food is being cooked.
	They’re the direct cause of browning and flavour formation after cooking.

	Maple products are made by the heating of maple sap. Maillard reactions can therefore be
	traced back to this process, where umami occurs with maple’s aromatic compounds. This is why
	Maple Products from Québec enhance the flavours of other foods, and are now found on
	the world’s finest tables. Maple’s complex aromas give chefs the ability
	to create dishes with new and original tastes.

	Surprisingly perhaps, Maple Products from Québec are chemically compatible with several
	essential ingredients found in Japanese cuisine. For example, food cooked with maple syrup,
	mirin and soy sauce has a decidedly enriched flavour. Other Maillard reactions occur when
	maple sugar reacts with the amino acids of mirin and soy. A striking example of umami in action!



Maple and Umami 







